div.p:
I thought I could not do less in Honour and Religion, (especially upon this Festival Occasion
                     •

               ) than to mind him of His Duty by the Discharge of my Own; but my Charity was not so well Requited, it seems, as it deserv'd: for instead of keeping himself to the Subject of the Wrong he had done me, he presently falls to his Old Play again, of throwing out Baits upon the Question of the Plot, to try if he could get any better hold of me This Bout than he did the last. Upon December 30. I received a Letter from him, in acknowledgment of mine of the 27th, in the Terms and Date following. Directed, For his Ever Honoured Friend, ROGER L'ESTRANGE, &c.
